  {
   "question": "Where does Feral (Bear) Druid Phase 3 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 233 top-ranked Feral (Bear) Druid DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 3 (Black Temple and Mount Hyjal), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Feral (Bear) Druid items in Phase 3?",
   "answer": "Vindicator's Dragonhide Bracers (91%), Idol of the Raven Goddess (74%), Belt of One-Hundred Deaths (72%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 3?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Black Temple and Mount Hyjal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Feral (Bear) Druid use in Phase 3?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Delicate Living Ruby, Shifting Nightseye and Glinting Noble Topaz in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Feral (Bear) Druid need in Phase 3?",
   "answer": "7 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of the Defender on head and Greater Inscription of Warding on shoulders. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of the Defender comes from Alurmi — Caverns of Time."
  }
